(35, '202304260730hydro1.jpg', 'Hydro facial', 'Hydro facial', '<span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">HydroFacial is a facial treatment combining six treatments in one that is suitable for everyone and their skin type. This treatment includes cleanse and peel, extract and hydrate &amp; infuse and protect and can be personalised to treat your skin concerns any skin type. It’s rejuvenating results are immediately visible, deep cleansing the skin from impurities and dead skin cells.</span>', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">What are the benefits of Hydro facial?</b></p><ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Improves overall skin texture</li><li>Improves skin hydration and radiance</li><li>Detoxifies the skin and gets rid of acne</li><li>Deep cleanses your skin for impurities</li><li>Minimises the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles</li><li>Suitable for all skin types</li></ul>', '<ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Consultation</li><li>Skin Analysis</li><li>Begin Your Treatment</li><li>Aftercare</li><li>Effective Results and Smooth Skin</li><li>Love the results? Why not purchase a discounted treatment package to continue your treatments every 4 weeks!</li></ul>', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Before Treatment</b></p><ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Avoid sun exposure and sunbed for one week before the treatment</li><li>Avoid chemical peels and laser treatments for two weeks before the treatment</li><li>Use sunscreen SPF30+ daily</li><li>Avoid exfoliating your skin for 48 hours prior to the treatment</li><li>Drink plenty of water</li><li>Avoid smoking of the day of your treatment</li></ul><p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">After Treatment</b></p><ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Avoid intense heat for 24 hours after the treatment</li><li>Avoid exercise, sauna, hot showers &amp; baths for 24 hours after the treatment</li><li>Avoid make up for the first 24 hours after treatment. Mineral make up may be used.</li><li>Avoid the use of any products containing tretinoin for 48 hours after the treatment</li><li>Avoid using acne medications for two days after the treatment</li><li>Avoid exfoliating and use of AHA or BHA, harsh exfoliants or acidic based products for 2-3 days (Glycolic, Lactic, Salicylic)</li><li>Do not use any Vitamin A/Retinol based products for 2-3 days (Retin A, Retinoic acid)</li><li>Do not rub, pick, or scratch the skin</li><li>Use sunscreen SPF50+ daily and avoid direct sun exposure, sunbeds, fake tan for 5 days after your treatment</li><li>Keep your skin hydrated and moisturised after the treatment daily using gentle cleansers and products</li></ul>', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b>.</b></p>', '<p><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">1.Is this treatment suitable for me?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. Hydrofacial is suitable for everyone of all ages and skin types, or if you have skin concerns including acne, dryness, wrinkles, blackheads, rosacea and pigmentation</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">2. Does it hurt?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. HydroFacial is not a painful treatment. You may feel light pressure from the wand during the procedure</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">3.How long does the treatment take?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. HydroFacial treatment takes around 45- 120 minutes</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">4. How long do the results last?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. This may vary from person to person, you can expect results to last for at least 7 days or much longer, you can have additional treatments to maintain those results</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">5. How many treatments do I need?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. You will see visible results immediately after the treatment. We recommend a course of 6 HydroFacial treatments every 4 weeks for optimum results</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">6.When can I not get the HydraFacial?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. Use of acne medication within the last six months, auto-immune disorders, pregnant or breastfeeding, recent cold sores, Botox or Fillers within the last two weeks, recent chemical peel, laser or waxing treatments, lymphatic disorders, active skin infections such as eczema, rash or wounds, scarring etc</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">7.What results can I expect?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. HydroFacial will leave your skin glowing, healthy, improving the skin’s texture and minimising the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">8.Are there any side effects?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. Side effects are minimum and last for a very short period of time. You can resume your normal daily activities after this treatment</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"></p>', '202304260730hydro2.jpg', '202304260730hydro3.jpg', NULL, NULL, '<ul class=\"marker-list-md\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; line-height: 22px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">Avoid heat for 24 hours after the treatment</li><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">Avoid exercise, sauna, hot showers &amp; baths for 24 hours after the treatment</li><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">Avoid make up for the first 24 hours after treatment. Mineral make up may be used.</li><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">Avoid the use of any products containing tretinoin for 48 hours after the treatment</li><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">Avoid using acne medications for two days after the treatment</li><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">Avoid exfoliating and use of AHA or BHA, harsh exfoliants or acidic based products for 2-3 days (Glycolic, Lactic, Salicylic)</li><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">Do not use any Vitamin A/Retinol based products for 2-3 days (Retin A, Retinoic acid)</li><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">Do not rub, pick, or scratch the skin</li><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">Use sunscreen SPF50+ daily and avoid direct sun exposure, sunbeds, fake tan for 5 days after your treatment</li><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px;\">Keep your skin hydrated and moisturised after the treatment daily using gentle cleansers and products</li></ul>', '202304260807aftercare5.jpg', '2023-04-24 05:39:04', '2023-04-26 02:37:18'),
(36, '202304260734laser-hair-1.jpg', 'Laser Hair Removal', 'Laser Hair Removal', '<span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">Laser Hair Removal is a safe and effective cosmetic procedure to eliminate unwanted hair from the body ensuring maximum results. If your hair is darker than your skin, we can treat you! We cannot treat grey, blonde, or red hair as the laser will not target them. We target the hair during the growth phase where the laser beam is absorbed by the dark pigment within the hair and then converted to heat destroying the hair follicle, leaving the surrounding area undamaged.</span>', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">What are the benefits of Laser Hair Removal</b></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"></p><ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Targets ingrown hair</li><li>Safe and effective</li><li>No downtime</li><li>Minimal discomfort</li><li>Long lasting results</li><li>Improves skin texture</li><li>Suitable for all skin types</li></ul>', '<ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Consultation</li><li>Skin Analysis</li><li>Patch Test</li><li>Purchase your treatment course and Aftercare</li><li>Begin your treatment plan</li><li>Continue your treatments every 6-8 weeks</li><li>Effective Results and Smooth Skin</li></ul>', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Before Treatment</b></p><ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Avoid sun exposure and sunbed for two weeks before the treatment</li><li>Use sunscreen SPF50+ daily</li><li>Exfoliating your skin and shave any hair 48 hours prior to the treatment</li><li>Wear loose clothing to your appointment</li><li>Drink plenty of water</li><li>Avoid smoking of the day of your treatment</li></ul><p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">After Treatment</b></p><ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Do not wax, pluck, or epilate any hair on the area treated, as this can stimulate hair growth. You are required to shave the area only</li><li>Avoid exercise, sauna, hot showers &amp; baths for 48 hours after the treatment</li><li>Exfoliate the area 2 weeks after the treatment</li><li>Avoid direct sun exposure for two – four weeks after the treatment and use sunscreen SPF50+ daily</li><li>Do not pick or scratch the treated area as this can cause scabbing lead to scarring</li><li>Avoid use of deodorants and other perspirants for 48 hours after the treatment</li><li>To soothe the skin, you can apply aloe vera gel and use vitamin E products if any pigmentation or discolouration occurs</li></ul>', '<ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Bikini Area</li><li>Hollywood</li><li>Brazilian</li><li>Underarms</li><li>Neck</li><li>Shoulders</li><li>Chest</li><li>Stomach</li><li>Hands/Feet</li><li>Back</li><li>Legs</li><li>Face</li></ul>', '<p><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">1. Is this treatment suitable for me?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A.Laser hair removal is suitable for anyone if you want to stop the hassle of waxing and shaving. Laser hair removal is great if you have ingrown hair.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">2.Does it hurt?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A.Most people describe the sensation as similar to that of a rubber band snapping onto the skin, but the discomfort is less than waxing and epilation treatments.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">3. Do I need a patch test?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. Yes a consultation and patch is required 48 hours prior to the treatment.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">4.How long does the treatment take?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. The average treatment time is around 20 minutes, depending on that size of area it can take up to 60 minutes.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">5.How long do the results last?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A.This may vary from person to person, you can expect results to last for up to two years with maintenance top up sessions.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">6.How many treatments do I need?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. As the hair growth grows in cycled stages 6-8 treatment sessions are recommended for optimum results.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">7.When can I not get the Laser Hair Removal?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A.During pregnancy, breastfeeding, tanned skin, keloid scarring, medical conditions such as vitiligo, reactions to histamines, recent peels or skin resurfacing treatments, skin disorders, photosensitive medication, lesions or open wounds, very dark skin, herpes and cold sores, epilepsy and hirsutism. Laser hair removal can be done on individuals 18 years and above.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">8.What results can I expect?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. Eradication of hair and smooth skin all year round.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">9.Are there any side effects?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A.Side effects include slight redness and tenderness of the area treated. It can also cause irritation temporarily but keep the area cool and moisturised will cause this to subside.</span><br></p>', '202304260734laser-hair-2.jpg', '202304260734laser-hair-3.jpg', NULL, NULL, '<ul style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; line-height: 22px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">Do not wax, pluck, or epilate any hair on the area treated, as this can stimulate hair growth. You are required to shave the area only</li><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">Avoid exercise, sauna, hot showers &amp; baths for 48 hours after the treatment</li><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">Exfoliate the area 2 weeks after the treatment</li><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">Avoid direct sun exposure for two – four weeks after the treatment and use sunscreen SPF50+ daily</li><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">Do not pick or scratch the treated area as this can cause scabbing lead to scarring</li><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">Avoid use of deodorants and other perspirants for 48 hours after the treatment</li><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px;\">To soothe the skin, you can apply aloe vera gel and use vitamin E products if any pigmentation or discolouration occurs</li></ul>', '202304260808aftercare2.jpg', '2023-04-25 04:17:37', '2023-04-26 02:38:38'),
(37, '202304260737laser-tatto-1.jpg', 'Laser Tattoo Removal', 'Laser Tattoo Removal', 'Laser Tattoo Removal is a safe and effective in removing multi coloured tattoos leaving the surrounding area undamaged. Using a concentrated bean of laser light to directly remove tattoos by simply heating the ink molecules and breaking them down into small particles, removing naturally through the body’s immune system. A gradual fading of the tattoo occurs over a series of treatments.', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">What are the benefits of Laser Tattoo Removal?</b></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"></p><ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>No scarring</li><li>Safe and effective</li><li>Minimal downtime</li></ul>', '<ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Consultation</li><li>Patch Test</li><li>Purchase your treatment course and Aftercare</li><li>Begin your treatment plan</li><li>Continue your treatments every 6-8 weeks</li><li>Effective Results and the tattoos gone!</li></ul>', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Before Treatment</b></p><ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Avoid sun exposure and sunbed for two weeks before the treatment</li><li>Do not add any lotions, perfumes, or creams to the area</li><li>Shave the area to be treated if there is hair present 12 hours prior treatment</li><li>Wear loose clothing to your appointment</li></ul><p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">After Treatment</b></p><ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Blisters can appear 8 hours&nbsp;after your laser tattoo removal treatment. If blisters are part of your healing process, they are normally held between 4-6 days and scabbing can last up to two weeks</li><li>Do not pick the scabs, blisters, or crusts&nbsp;that form after your laser tattoo removal treatment. Picking at the skin directly relates to any scarring that may occur</li><li>Use sunscreen to protect the area&nbsp;treated for at least 3 months after each session</li><li>Do not apply make-up or anything that may irritate the healing area. Scented products can irritate healing skin</li><li>Avoid sauna, hot showers &amp; baths for after the treatment until the area has healed</li><li>If you experience discomfort use an ice pack for 5-10 minutes after the treatment</li></ul>', '<ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Neck</li><li>Shoulders</li><li>Chest</li><li>Stomach</li><li>Hands/Feet</li><li>Back</li><li>Legs</li><li>Face</li></ul>', '<p><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">1.Is this treatment suitable for me?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A.Anyone from the age of 18 years and above can get their tattoo removed subject to no contra-indications to the treatment.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">2. Does it hurt?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. The sensation as like a hot pin prick or the flick of an elastic band. Whilst mildly uncomfortable, most people tolerate treatment well. A skin cooling device may be utilised to reduce any discomfort.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">3.Do I need a patch test?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A.Yes, a consultation and patch are required 48 hours prior to the treatment.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">4.How long does the treatment take?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A.The average treatment time is around 20 minutes, depending on that size of area it can take up to 30 minutes.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">5.How many treatments do I need?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. 4-6 treatment sessions are recommended for optimum results.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">6. When can I not get the Laser Tattoo Removal?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. During pregnancy, breastfeeding, tanned skin, keloid scarring, epilepsy, skin conditions such as eczema, haemophilia, diabetes insulin dependent, chemotherapy, liver disease, previous allergic reaction to tattoo removal, auto immune disorders, vitiligo, implants or pacemakers, blood thinning medication and photosensitive medication</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">7.What results can I expect?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A.Successful removal of the unwanted tattoo</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">8.Are there any side effects?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A.Very rarely the skin may become lighter or darker, or a small blister may form. Change to skin texture and scarring is possible, though uncommon, and is more likely if any grazes are not allowed to heal naturally. There may be loss of the natural tanning ability in the area treated, which usually improves with time</span><br></p>', '202304260737laser-tatto-2.jpg', '202304260737laser-tatto-3.jpg', NULL, NULL, '<ul class=\"marker-list-md\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; line-height: 22px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">Blisters can appear 8 hours after your laser tattoo removal treatment. If blisters are part of your healing process, they are normally held between 4-6 days and scabbing can last up to two weeks</li><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">Do not pick the scabs, blisters, or crusts that form after your laser tattoo removal treatment. Picking at the skin directly relates to any scarring that may occur</li><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">Use sunscreen to protect the area treated for at least 3 months after each session</li><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">Do not apply make-up or anything that may irritate the healing area. Scented products can irritate healing skin</li><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">Avoid sauna, hot showers &amp; baths for after the treatment until the area has healed</li><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px;\">If you experience discomfort use an ice pack for 5-10 minutes after the treatment</li></ul>', '202304260810aftercare3.jpg', '2023-04-26 02:07:21', '2023-04-26 02:40:25'),
(38, '202304260743laser-surface-1.jpg', 'Laser Resurfacing Skin Treatment', 'Laser Resurfacing Skin Treatment', 'Laser Skin Resurfacing provides total rejuvenation to give the skin a smooth, youthful, and glowing appearance. The laser light heat metabolises unhealthy cells and causes stimulations to produce healthy new cells over a series of treatments. The surrounding non affected areas of skin aid the body’s natural recovery process, allowing dramatic results without significant downtime', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">What are the benefits of Laser Resurfacing Skin Treatment?</b></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"></p><ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>No scarring</li><li>Safe and effective</li><li>Minimal downtime</li><li>Improves skin texture and appearance</li></ul>', '<ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Consultation</li><li>Skin Analysis</li><li>Patch Test</li><li>Purchase your treatment course and Aftercare</li><li>Begin your treatment plan</li><li>Continue your treatments every 6-8 weeks</li><li>Effective Results and improved skin appearance!</li></ul>', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Before Treatment</b></p><ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Avoid sun exposure and sunbed for two weeks before the treatment</li><li>Do not add any lotions, perfumes, or creams to the area</li><li>Use sunscreen SPF50+ daily</li><li>Wear loose clothing to your appointment</li><li>Drink plenty of water</li></ul><p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">After Treatment</b></p><ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Avoid direct sun exposure for two – four weeks after the treatment and use sunscreen SPF50+ daily</li><li>For one week do not apply make-up or anything that may irritate the healing area. Scented products can irritate healing skin</li><li>To reduce any erythema or inflammation apply a cold compress to the area for 5-10 minutes after the treatment</li><li>Keep your skin hydrated and moisturised after the treatment daily using gentle cleansers and products</li><li>Avoid heat for 24 hours after the treatment</li><li>Avoid exfoliating and use of AHA or BHA, harsh exfoliants or acidic based products for 2-3 days (Glycolic, Lactic, Salicylic)</li><li>Avoid the use of any products containing tretinoin for 48 hours after the treatment</li><li>Avoid exercise, sauna, hot showers &amp; baths for 24 hours after the treatment</li></ul>', '<ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Neck</li><li>Shoulders</li><li>Chest</li><li>Stomach</li><li>Hands/Feet</li><li>Back</li><li>Legs</li><li>Face</li></ul>', '<p><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">1.Is this treatment suitable for me?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A.Anyone from the age of 18 years and above can get skin resurfacing subject to no contra-indications to the treatment. Treatment is suitable for most people and highly recommended for individuals wanting a brighter, more even skin tone, smoother skin texture with improved skin elasticity, a reduction of wrinkles, reduced pore size and stretch marks</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">2.Does it hurt?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. A warm, heating sensation is felt during treatment, with some mild stinging. After treatment the skin can be quite hot and so cooling packs are often utilised to minimise discomfort.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">3. Do I need a patch test?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A.Yes, a consultation and patch are required 48 hours prior to the treatment.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">4.How long does the treatment take?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A.The average treatment time is around 20 minutes, depending on that size of area it can take up to 30 minutes.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">5.How many treatments do I need?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. 4-6 treatment sessions are recommended for optimum results.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">6.When can I not get the Laser Skin Resurfacing?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. During pregnancy, breastfeeding, tanned skin, keloid scarring, epilepsy, skin conditions such as eczema, haemophilia, diabetes insulin dependent, chemotherapy, liver disease, previous allergic reaction to tattoo removal, auto immune disorders, vitiligo, implants or pacemakers, blood thinning medication and photosensitive medication</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">7. What results can I expect?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A.Improved skin texture and appearance</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">8.Are there any side effects?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A.Skin redness, swelling and the bronzing appearance described above are all expected outcomes of treatment. Other unwanted effects are rare but can include a small blisters or temporary change to skin pigmentation, such as a darkening of the skin</span><br></p>', '202304260743laser-surface-2.jpg', '202304260743laser-surface-4.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-04-26 02:13:58', '2023-04-26 02:13:58'),
(39, '202304260746laser-rejuvenation-1.jpg', 'Laser Skin Rejuvenation', 'Laser Skin Rejuvenation', 'Laser Skin Rejuvenation is great if you’re looking to enhance your skin complexion and signs of aging giving the skin a smooth, youthful, and glowing appearance. Precisely controlled short pulses of light are released that target discolouration (brown and red lesions) to create a more youthful, even complexion. In addition, this light results in the stimulation of the fibroblast cells, leading to increased production of new collagen and elastin', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">What are the benefits of Laser Skin Rejuvenation?</b></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"></p><ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Minimises pores</li><li>Safe and effective</li><li>Minimal downtime</li><li>Improves skin texture and appearance</li><li>Improved complexion reducing fine lines and wrinkles</li></ul>', '<ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Consultation</li><li>Skin Analysis</li><li>Patch Test</li><li>Purchase your treatment course and Aftercare</li><li>Begin your treatment plan</li><li>Continue your treatments every 6-8 weeks</li><li>Effective Results and glowing appearance!</li></ul>', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Before Treatment</b></p><ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Avoid sun exposure and sunbed for two weeks before the treatment</li><li>Do not add any lotions, perfumes, or creams to the area</li><li>Use sunscreen SPF50+ daily</li><li>Wear loose clothing to your appointment</li><li>Drink plenty of water</li></ul><p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; lin