olor: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">2.Does it hurt?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. Treatment can be mildly uncomfortable, but no anaesthesia is required, and most people describe the discomfort as moderate and acceptable, not unlike a quick pin prick and warm feeling.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">3.Do I need a patch test?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A.Yes, a consultation and patch are required 48 hours prior to the treatment.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">4.How long does the treatment take?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A.The average treatment time is around 20 minutes, depending on that size of area it can take up to 30 minutes.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">5.How many treatments do I need?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. 4-6 treatment sessions are recommended for optimum results.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">6.When can I not get the Laser Skin Rejuvenation?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. During pregnancy, breastfeeding, tanned skin, keloid scarring, epilepsy, skin conditions such as eczema, haemophilia, diabetes insulin dependent, chemotherapy, liver disease, previous allergic reaction to tattoo removal, auto immune disorders, vitiligo, implants or pacemakers, blood thinning medication and photosensitive medication</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">7.What results can I expect?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A.Improved and firmer skin appearance and reduction in fine lines</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">8.Are there any side effects?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A.The skin may be quite red and slightly swollen after treatment, but this usually subsides quickly. Very rarely a small blister may form and there can be temporary lightening or darkening of the skin. However, most people experience no side effects, and any skin reaction usually disappears within a few hours.</span><br></p>', '202304260746laser-rejuvenation-2.jpg', '202304260746laser-rejuvenation-3.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-04-26 02:16:56', '2023-04-26 02:16:56');
