(40, '202304260750laser-vein-1.jpg', 'Laser Thread Veins Removal', 'Laser Thread Veins Removal', 'Laser Thread Vein Removal clears your complexion from visible veins, redness or broken capillaries also known as spider veins. Laser is the safest and effective way to diminish the veins as the laser light treats the target area and coagulates the blood vessels. The body then disperses them through the lymphatic system through a series of treatments.', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">What are the benefits of Laser Thread Veins Removal?</b></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"></p><ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Reduce redness and rosacea</li><li>Safe and effective</li><li>Minimal downtime</li><li>Reduce the visibility of veins</li><li>Improved complexion</li></ul>', '<ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Consultation</li><li>Skin Analysis</li><li>Patch Test</li><li>Purchase your treatment course and Aftercare</li><li>Begin your treatment plan</li><li>Continue your treatments every 6-8 weeks</li><li>Effective Results and no visible veins!</li></ul>', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Before Treatment</b></p><ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Avoid sun exposure and sunbed for two weeks before the treatment</li><li>Do not add any lotions, perfumes, or creams to the area</li><li>Use sunscreen SPF50+ daily</li><li>Wear loose clothing to your appointment</li></ul><p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">After Treatment</b></p><ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Avoid direct sun exposure for two – four weeks after the treatment and use sunscreen SPF50+ daily</li><li>For one week do not apply make-up or anything that may irritate the healing area. Scented products can irritate healing skin</li><li>To reduce any erythema or inflammation apply a cold compress to the area for 5-10 minutes after the treatment</li><li>Keep your skin hydrated and moisturised after the treatment daily using gentle cleansers and products</li><li>Avoid heat for 24 hours after the treatment</li><li>Avoid exfoliating and use of AHA or BHA, harsh exfoliants or acidic based products for 2-3 days (Glycolic, Lactic, Salicylic)</li><li>Avoid the use of any products containing tretinoin for 48 hours after the treatment</li><li>Avoid acne medication for two days</li><li>Avoid exercise, sauna, hot showers &amp; baths for 24 hours after the treatment</li></ul>', '<ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Neck</li><li>Shoulders</li><li>Chest</li><li>Stomach</li><li>Hands/Feet</li><li>Back</li><li>Legs</li><li>Face</li></ul>', '<p><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">1.Is this treatment suitable for me?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A.Anyone from the age of 18 years and above can get thread vein removal subject to no contra-indications to the treatment. Treatment is suitable for most people and highly recommended for individuals wanting a brighter, more even skin tone and reduction of wrinkles, reduced pore size.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">2.Does it hurt?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. Treatment can be mildly uncomfortable, but no anaesthesia is required, and most people describe the discomfort as moderate and acceptable, not unlike a quick pin prick and warm feeling.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">3.Do I need a patch test?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A.Yes, a consultation and patch are required 48 hours prior to the treatment.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">4.How long does the treatment take?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A.The average treatment time is around 20 minutes, depending on that size of area it can take up to 30 minutes.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">5.How many treatments do I need?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A.4-6 treatment sessions are recommended for optimum results.</span><br style=\"color: 