(43, '202304260759laser-fungal-1.jpg', 'Laser Fungal Nail Treatment', 'Laser Fungal Nail Treatment', 'Laser Nail fungus Treatment works safely and effectively to treat fungal nail infections. The laser penetrates, generating heat beneath the nail plate where the infection is present and destroying the fugus cells. As the nails grows out, any damage from the fungus will gradually disappear.', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">What are the benefits of Laser Fungal Nail Treatment?</b></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"></p><ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Treating fungus present in nails</li><li>Safe and effective</li><li>Minimal downtime</li><li>Healthy growth of the nail</li></ul>', '<ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Consultation</li><li>Nail analysis to confirm infection</li><li>Patch Test</li><li>Purchase your treatment course and Aftercare</li><li>Begin your treatment plan</li><li>Continue your treatments every 6-8 weeks</li><li>Effective Results and destruction of fungus!</li></ul>', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Before Treatment</b></p><ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Your nails must be free from polish or any coatings</li><li>Your nails must be trimmed short</li><li>Keep your nails as clean as possible</li></ul><p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 27px; line-height: 27px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">After Treatment</b></p><ul style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li>Keep the nails cut short as possible</li><li>Use anti-fungal shoe spray before wearing your shoes</li><li>Foot soak with sea salts 3 times a week (ask technician for in salon treatments)</li><li>Apply tea tree oil directly on the nails via a cotton swab just before wearing your socks. opt for cotton socks</li><li>Thoroughly dry your feet whenever wet</li><li>Wear shoes that breathe</li><li>Avoid wearing nail polish until infection has cleared</li></ul>', '<p>.</p>', '<p><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">1.Is this treatment suitable for me?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. Anyone from the age of 18 years and above can get nail fungus treatment subject to no contra-indications to the treatment.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">2.Does it hurt?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A.A degree of heating and some discomfort is felt during treatment. However, a skin cooling device can be used to make treatment as comfortable as possible.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">3.Do I need a patch test?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A.Yes, a consultation and patch are required 48 hours prior to the treatment.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">4.How long does the treatment take?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A.Treatments generally take in the region of 30 minutes</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">5.How many treatments do I need?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. Treatments are conducted every 6 to 8 weeks depending on the area being treated. The number of treatments required varies, although typically 2 - 6 treatments are needed for optimum results. These results become apparent as the nail grows out, and due to the slow rate of growth of toenails it may take several months for the full results to become apparent.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">6.When can I not get the Laser Acne Removal?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. During pregnancy, breastfeeding, tanned skin, keloid scarring, epilepsy, skin conditions such as eczema, haemophilia, diabetes insulin dependent, chemotherapy, liver disease, previous allergic reaction to tattoo removal, auto immune disorders, vitiligo, implants or pacemakers, blood thinning medication and photosensitive medication</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">7.What results can I expect?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. Reduction of fungus and healthy growth of nail</span><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><b style=\"font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">8.Are there any side effects?</b><br style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">A. The side-effects of laser treatments are generally mild and transient (unlike the side-effects of some of the medications used to treat fungal infections). The area may be red immediately after treatment and may be a little swollen and tender, but this usually subsides within a few hours. Unwanted reactions are rare but may include a small blister in the area around the nail, or temporary lightening or darkening of the skin. In rare cases, if the nail is very badly infected, the nail may fall off, but if this occurs, it will be replaced by a smoother, uninfected nail.</span><br></p>', '202304260759laser-fungal-2.jpg', '202304260759laser-fungal-3.jpg', NULL, NULL, '<ul class=\"marker-list-md\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; line-height: 22px; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">Keep the nails cut short as possible</li><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">Use anti-fungal shoe spray before wearing your shoes</li><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">Foot soak with sea salts 3 times a week (ask technician for in salon treatments)</li><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">Apply tea tree oil directly on the nails via a cotton swab just before wearing your socks. opt for cotton socks</li><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">Thoroughly dry your feet whenever wet</li><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">Wear shoes that breathe</li><li style=\"position: relative; padding-left: 24px;\">Avoid wearing nail polish until infection has cleared</li></ul>', '202304260815aftercare1.jpg', '2023-04-26 02:29:32', '2023-04-26 02:45:35');

